# --- paste into ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md (always-on) instead of using the skill ---
# A skill is loaded only when the model judges it relevant; this snippet is
# always in context, so it fires more reliably for proactive "alert me" behavior.

## Voice alerts — speak up with `vox` when I need to act

When something needs my attention and I might not be watching the terminal, say
it out loud with `vox` (a local text-to-speech CLI; https://github.com/kohlhofer/vox).
I often have several long jobs going at once, so the note has to tell me *which*
one without making me come look.

**Speak — and basically only — when:** a long task I'm waiting on finishes
(passed or failed); you're blocked and need my input/decision/approval;
something broke I'd want to know about now. Stay silent for routine progress,
ordinary replies, and anything I'm already watching.

**What to say:** one short, conversational sentence (~6–14 words). Lead with the
concern (project/repo/process) so I can tell it apart from my other jobs; say
what happened and what you need. Headline only — never read out long messages,
errors, logs, or status; those stay on screen.

**How:** guard with `command -v vox` (silent no-op if absent); fire-and-return,
no `--wait`. Example:
`command -v vox >/dev/null && vox "The web build finished — 2 tests failed."`
